00:22:09,840 --> 00:22:13,830
it must have been my
seventh birthday I think,

514
00:22:13,830 --> 00:22:18,830
and my parents had put a
trampoline in the garden.

515
00:22:19,350 --> 00:22:20,970
And I kid you not,

516
00:22:20,970 --> 00:22:24,120
I spent every waking
hour on that trampoline.

517
00:22:24,120 --> 00:22:26,430
I absolutely loved it.

518
00:22:26,430 --> 00:22:29,160
- [Will] 73, what was
your relationship like

519
00:22:29,160 --> 00:22:31,710
with your sibling when
you were both growing up?

520
00:22:31,710 --> 00:22:32,820
- Well, it was funny

521
00:22:32,820 --> 00:22:35,310
because I was five
years older than George.

522
00:22:35,310 --> 00:22:38,610
That's a big gap when
one is two and one is six

523
00:22:38,610 --> 00:22:40,830
or when one is 10 and one is 14.

524
00:22:40,830 --> 00:22:43,500
So we weren't so close as children.

525
00:22:43,500 --> 00:22:46,350
It's only now we are adults
that we are really close.

526
00:22:46,350 --> 00:22:48,270
- [Will] 74, what's the best thing

527
00:22:48,270 --> 00:22:51,393
that's ever happened to you
and how did it make you feel?

528
00:22:52,530 --> 00:22:53,550
- Getting married.

529
00:22:53,550 --> 00:22:57,090
I just felt high on life.

530
00:22:57,090 --> 00:22:59,340
I was so unbelievably happy.

531
00:22:59,340 --> 00:23:01,920
I got to marry the man of my dreams

532
00:23:01,920 --> 00:23:05,520
and be surrounded by everyone I loved.

533
00:23:05,520 --> 00:23:07,890
And it was just after COVID,

534
00:23:07,890 --> 00:23:09,996
so it was the first time
I'd seen so many people

535
00:23:09,996 --> 00:23:11,730
in over two years.

536
00:23:11,730 --> 00:23:13,800
- [Will] 75, what's one challenge

537
00:23:13,800 --> 00:23:15,900
or obstacle you faced in your life

538
00:23:15,900 --> 00:23:17,400
and how did you overcome it?

539
00:23:17,400 --> 00:23:19,350
- I was really ill as a teenager.

540
00:23:19,350 --> 00:23:20,599
From the age of 14 to 16,

541
00:23:20,599 --> 00:23:22,500
I had glandular fever

542
00:23:22,500 --> 00:23:26,756
and then a weird post-viral
chronic fatigue thing,

543
00:23:26,756 --> 00:23:28,470
and it wiped me out,

544
00:23:28,470 --> 00:23:32,340
and it was a rubbish time
and I was very depressed.

545
00:23:32,340 --> 00:23:36,300
It's such a blur that I don't
even know how I overcame it.

546
00:23:36,300 --> 00:23:38,910
I just know that I had a lot
of support from my family.

547
00:23:38,910 --> 00:23:41,490
- [Will] 76, do you
have any personal goals

548
00:23:41,490 --> 00:23:43,536
or aspirations that
you're working towards?

549
00:23:43,536 --> 00:23:47,220
- Oh, a big goal is to have a happy family

550
00:23:47,220 --> 00:23:48,720
with a couple of children.

551
00:23:48,720 --> 00:23:51,090
- [Will] 77, what's one
thing you're proud of

552
00:23:51,090 --> 00:23:53,271
or accomplished recently outside of work?

553
00:23:53,271 --> 00:23:56,850
- I've made some pretty big
charity donations this year

554
00:23:56,850 --> 00:23:59,730
that I am personally
very proud of, I think.

555
00:23:59,730 --> 00:24:02,453
- [Will] 78, who's one
person that's influenced

556
00:24:02,453 --> 00:24:06,153
or inspired you and how have
they impacted your life?

557
00:24:07,350 --> 00:24:09,600
- My dad because he's so supportive,

558
00:24:09,600 --> 00:24:11,218
so kind, so encouraging,

559
00:24:11,218 --> 00:24:14,370
and that's how I hope to be.

560
00:24:14,370 --> 00:24:16,500
- [Will] 79, what's one thing you've done

561
00:24:16,500 --> 00:24:19,261
for someone else recently
and how did it make you feel?

562
00:24:19,261 --> 00:24:22,117
- I helped someone very close with me

563
00:24:22,117 --> 00:24:24,550
achieve something they've
wanted to do for a long time,

564
00:24:24,550 --> 00:24:26,482
and it made me feel really good.

565
00:24:26,482 --> 00:24:28,110
And that's all I can say.

566
00:24:28,110 --> 00:24:30,540
- [Will] 80, what's one
thing you've learned in life

567
00:24:30,540 --> 00:24:32,660
that's helped you grow or
become a better person?

568
00:24:32,660 --> 00:24:37,530
- Not everyone is going to
like you, and that is okay.

569
00:24:37,530 --> 00:24:41,640
- [Will] Ninth topic,
technology small talk questions.

570
00:24:41,640 --> 00:24:45,150
Question 81, what's one
technology or gadget

571
00:24:45,150 --> 00:24:47,610
you can't live without, and why?

572
00:24:47,610 --> 00:24:49,020
