578
00:25:01,470 --> 00:25:02,848
and I've found it really good,

579
00:25:02,848 --> 00:25:05,670
although the battery life is terrible.

580
00:25:05,670 --> 00:25:07,370
- [Will] 83, do you prefer Apple

581
00:25:07,370 --> 00:25:09,437
or Android products, and why?

582
00:25:09,437 --> 00:25:11,799
- I prefer Apple products.

583
00:25:11,799 --> 00:25:16,620
I think they are really
user-friendly, and unfortunately,

584
00:25:16,620 --> 00:25:18,690
I love the way they all
connect with each other.

585
00:25:18,690 --> 00:25:21,270
- [Will] 84, have you
ever built or customised

586
00:25:21,270 --> 00:25:24,435
a computer or device
and how did it turn out?

587
00:25:24,435 --> 00:25:26,460
- No, I've never done that.

588
00:25:26,460 --> 00:25:28,272
I would be interested in learning though.

589
00:25:28,272 --> 00:25:31,555
- [Will] 85, what's one recent
technological advancement

590
00:25:31,555 --> 00:25:34,950
or development that you find interesting?

591
00:25:34,950 --> 00:25:37,707
- AI, definitely artificial intelligence.

592
00:25:37,707 --> 00:25:40,650
I feel like we're on the
cusp of something amazing.

593
00:25:40,650 --> 00:25:42,570
This is the worst it's ever going to be.

594
00:25:42,570 --> 00:25:44,820
It's only going to get better,

595
00:25:44,820 --> 00:25:48,060
and I feel you have to
keep up or get left behind.

596
00:25:48,060 --> 00:25:50,629
- [Will] 86, have you
tried virtual reality

597
00:25:50,629 --> 00:25:54,249
or augmented reality, and
what's your experience like?

598
00:25:54,249 --> 00:25:57,840
- I have, very briefly at an event,

599
00:25:57,840 --> 00:25:59,250
and I thought it was amazing.

600
00:25:59,250 --> 00:26:00,660
I'd love to explore it more.

601
00:26:00,660 --> 00:26:04,142
- [Will] 87, what's one useful
app or tool you use regularly

602
00:26:04,142 --> 00:26:06,090
and how does it help you?

603
00:26:06,090 --> 00:26:09,240
- I use an app to track
my menstrual cycle,

604
00:26:09,240 --> 00:26:12,210
and it helps me understand

605
00:26:12,210 --> 00:26:14,370
why I'm feeling rubbish some days.

606
00:26:14,370 --> 00:26:17,202
- [Will] 88, do you think
technology has more positive

607
00:26:17,202 --> 00:26:20,220
or negative effects on our lives, and why?

608
00:26:20,220 --> 00:26:22,770
- I would say in the grand
scheme of things, positive.

609
00:26:22,770 --> 00:26:24,406
There are lots of negative parts,

610
00:26:24,406 --> 00:26:28,530
but definitely for medical
advancements, positive.

611
00:26:28,530 --> 00:26:30,998
- [Will] 89, what's
one technological issue

612
00:26:30,998 --> 00:26:34,200
or challenge that you
wish could be solved?

613
00:26:34,200 --> 00:26:36,252
- My internet connection, please.

614
00:26:36,252 --> 00:26:37,916
I can't believe it's 2023,

615
00:26:37,916 --> 00:26:39,859
and in rural parts of the UK,

616
00:26:39,859 --> 00:26:44,190
you still can't get
solid, reliable internet.

617
00:26:44,190 --> 00:26:46,841
- [Will] 90, do you have
any tips or recommendations

618
00:26:46,841 --> 00:26:49,800
for staying safe and secure online?

619
00:26:49,800 --> 00:26:52,350
- Don't trust anyone.

620
00:26:52,350 --> 00:26:54,000
There are so many scammers.

621
00:26:54,000 --> 00:26:57,270
If it sounds too good to
be true, it probably is.

622
00:26:57,270 --> 00:27:01,080
- [Will] 10th topic, lifestyle
small talk questions.

623
00:27:01,080 --> 00:27:04,710
Question 91, what's your
typical daily routine

624
00:27:04,710 --> 00:27:06,777
and how do you make the most of your time?

625
00:27:06,777 --> 00:27:09,870
- We normally wake up at around 6:30.

626
00:27:09,870 --> 00:27:13,050
I nearly always have
porridge for breakfast,

627
00:27:13,050 --> 00:27:15,660
lunch between midday and one,

628
00:27:15,660 --> 00:27:18,630
and dinner between six and eight.

629
00:27:18,630 --> 00:27:19,920
That's a bit random.

630
00:27:19,920 --> 00:27:22,050
And I make the most of my time

631
00:27:22,050 --> 00:27:25,802
by trying to get as much done
in the morning as possible.

632
00:27:25,802 --> 00:27:29,640
- [Will] 92, do you prefer
to stay in or go out,

633
00:27:29,640 --> 00:27:32,441
and what do you enjoy doing
during your free time?

634
00:27:32,441 --> 00:27:34,175
- Oh, I like a balance of both.

635
00:27:34,175 --> 00:27:37,024
I end up getting really
stale if I stay in too much.

636
00:27:37,024 --> 00:27:39,120
I love going out of the weekends

637
00:27:39,120 --> 00:27:40,613
and staying in during the week.

638
00:27:40,613 --> 00:27:43,320
- [Will] 93, what's one activity or hobby

639
00:27:43,320 --> 00:27:45,764
you find most relaxing
or stress relieving?

640
00:27:45,764 --> 00:27:48,690
- I don't know if it's a
hobby, it's an activity,

641
00:27:48,690 --> 00:27:53,690
but taking a bath, and
especially a bath with a view.

642
00:27:54,246 --> 00:27:56,400
I have a bath near a window,

643
00:27:56,400 --> 00:27:58,140
and sometimes there
are sheep in the field,

644
00:27:58,140 --> 00:27:59,497
and it's just lovely.

645
00:27:59,497 --> 00:28:02,241
- [Will] 94, do you have
any daily rituals or habits

646
00:28:02,241 --> 00:28:04,320
that you swear by?

647
00:28:04,320 --> 00:28:09,270
- I have a coffee in bed every
morning, and I love that.

648
00:28:09,270 --> 00:28:13,414
I love that little 20-minute
period of waking up,

649
00:28:13,414 --> 00:28:14,640
having a coffee.

650
00:28:14,640 --> 00:28:15,600
I know lots of people say

651
00:28:15,600 --> 00:28:17,490
you shouldn't have it
first thing in the morning,

652
00:28:17,490 --> 00:28:19,713
but it works for me, and
it makes me feel good.

653
00:28:19,713 --> 00:28:23,910
- [Will] 95, what do you
typically have for lunch?

654
00:28:23,910 --> 00:28:26,981
- I normally have soup in the winter

655
00:28:26,981 --> 00:28:29,334
or a salad in the summer.

656
00:28:29,334 --> 00:28:31,470
- [Will] 96, what's one way

657
00:28:31,470 --> 00:28:33,350
you like to stay active or healthy,

658
00:28:33,350 --> 00:28:36,060
